<glossentry id="dita-ot-dir">
  <glossterm>DITA_OT_DIR</glossterm>
  <glossdef><p><filepath>DITA_OT_DIR</filepath> is the default directory that is specified for your DITA Open
      Toolkit distribution in the <xref
        href="../topics/preferences-dita.dita#preferences-dita/DITA-OT-section"><menucascade
          product="author developer editor">
          <uicontrol>Options</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>DITA</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><menucascade product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
          <uicontrol>DITA</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> preferences page</xref>.</p><p>For example, if you are using DITA 1.8, the default DITA OT directory is: <filepath><term
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>/frameworks/dita/DITA-OT</filepath> (or
      if you are using DITA 2.x, <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
        />/frameworks/dita/DITA-OT2.x</filepath>). You can also specify a custom directory.</p></glossdef>
</glossentry>